Certainly! Below is a simple HTML file that serves as a web app to advise users on what cheese to eat based on the time of day and the type of wine they have. The app uses embedded CSS for styling and JavaScript for functionality. You can copy and paste this code into an HTML file and open it in a web browser.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Cheese and Wine Advisor</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            background-color: #f4f4f4;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 20px;
        }
        h1 {
            text-align: center;
            color: #333;
        }
        .container {
            max-width: 600px;
            margin: auto;
            background: white;
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 8px;
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }
        label {
            display: block;
            margin: 10px 0 5px;
        }
        select, button {
            width: 100%;
            padding: 10px;
            margin: 10px 0;
            border: 1px solid #ccc;
            border-radius: 4px;
        }
        .result {
            margin-top: 20px;
            padding: 10px;
            background: #e7f3fe;
            border-left: 6px solid #2196F3;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="container">
    <h1>Cheese and Wine Advisor</h1>
    <label for="time">Select Time of Day:</label>
    <select id="time">
        <option value="morning">Morning</option>
        <option value="afternoon">Afternoon</option>
        <option value="evening">Evening</option>
        <option value="night">Night</option>
    </select>

    <label for="wine">Select Type of Wine:</label>
    <select id="wine">
        <option value="red">Red</option>
        <option value="white">White</option>
        <option value="rosé">Rosé</option>
        <option value="sparkling">Sparkling</option>
    </select>

    <button onclick="adviseCheese()">Get Cheese Recommendation</button>

    <div class="result" id="result"></div>
</div>

<script>
    function adviseCheese() {
        const time = document.getElementById('time').value;
        const wine = document.getElementById('wine').value;
        let cheeseRecommendation = '';

        if (time === 'morning') {
            cheeseRecommendation = 'Cream Cheese or Ricotta';
        } else if (time === 'afternoon') {
            cheeseRecommendation = 'Cheddar or Gouda';
        } else if (time === 'evening') {
            cheeseRecommendation = 'Brie or Camembert';
        } else if (time === 'night') {
            cheeseRecommendation = 'Blue Cheese or Aged Cheddar';
        }

        if (wine === 'red') {
            cheeseRecommendation += ' pairs well with a strong cheese.';
        } else if (wine === 'white') {
            cheeseRecommendation += ' pairs well with a mild cheese.';
        } else if (wine === 'rosé') {
            cheeseRecommendation += ' pairs well with a semi-soft cheese.';
        } else if (wine === 'sparkling') {
            cheeseRecommendation += ' pairs well with a fresh cheese.';
        }

        document.getElementById('result').innerText = cheeseRecommendation;
    }
</script>

</body>
</html>
```

### How to Use:
1. Copy the code above and paste it into a text editor.
2. Save the file with a `.html` extension, for example, `cheese_wine_advisor.html`.
3. Open the saved file in a web browser.
4. Select the time of day and the type of wine, then click the button to get a cheese recommendation!
